.TH SFTPFS 4
.SH NAME
sftpfs \- sftp file server client
.SH SYNOPSIS
mount {
.B sftpfs
[
.B -dD
] [
.B -s
.I sshcmd
|
.I addr
] [
.I remotepath
]
}
mtpt
.SH DESCRIPTION
.I Sftpfs
translates between styx messages and sftp (version 3) messages.  If
.I addr
is specified,
.IR ssh (1)
is executed to connect to the address request the sftp subsystem.
Otherwise
.I sshcmd
specified with
.B -s
is executed.
The home directory on the remote server is mounted by default,
another directory (relative to the home directory) can be specified by
.IR remotepath .
Option
.B -d
causes debug messages to be printed.
Option
.B -D
causes sftp message traces to be printed.
.SH EXAMPLE
Mount files from ``dis'':
.EX
	mount -c {sftpfs dis} /n/dis
.EE
.SH SEE ALSO
.IR mount (1),
.IR ssh (1).
.IR 
.SH SOURCE
.B /appl/cmd/sftpfs.b
.SH BUGS
See the ``todo'' section in the README for now.
